BT /F2 20 Tf 40 744 Td (CloudLearn Simulator - Low Level Design) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 40 724 Td (Local-first cloud simulator with AWS-compatible workflows and pluggable runtime bundles) Tj ET
q 0.70 0.74 0.80 rg 40 714 532 1.2 re f Q
BT /F2 14 Tf 40 700 Td (1. Objective) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 40 680 Td
(CloudLearn is a local-first cloud simulator that gives users an AWS-like experience for) Tj
T* (learning, app validation, and workflow practice without cloud hosting or cloud licenses.) Tj
ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 40 612 Td (2. Design Principles) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 40 592 Td (- Simulate the workflow, not the internal AWS implementation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 40 578 Td (- Keep the core provider-neutral so Azure and GCP can be added later.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 40 564 Td (- Prefer lightweight local implementations over heavy emulation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 40 550 Td (- Persist state locally so simulator restarts preserve workflows.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 40 536 Td (- Expose AWS compatibility at the adapter boundary.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 40 522 Td (- Treat runtime environments as pluggable bundles.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 40 420 Td (3. What the product must do) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 40 400 Td (- Run entirely on the user's machine.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 40 386 Td (- Expose AWS-compatible APIs for common workflows.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 40 372 Td (- Provide lightweight runtime environments for Java, .NET, Go, PHP, and Python.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 40 358 Td (- Support local start, stop, and resume with durable state.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 40 344 Td (- Allow optional validation against real AWS.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 40 330 Td (- Export and import desired state through Terraform later.) Tj ET
q 0.82 0.82 0.82 rg 40 28 532 0.8 re f Q
BT /F1 9 Tf 40 16 Td (CloudLearn LLD) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 526 16 Td (Page 1) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
